# Data Structures and Algorithms III

<span class="lead"> </span>

## [Hash Tables I](../module/recLpJY4yFQcV3qeW)

#### Objectives:

- Student should be able to recall the time and space complexity, the strengths and weaknesses, and the common uses of a hash table
- Student should be able to describe and implement a hash function
- Student should be able to implement a user-defined HashTable class that allows basic operations

## [Hash Tables II](../module/recG6onEnlSOWziKO)

#### Objectives:

- Student should be able to understand hash collisions and use a linked list for collision resolution in a user-defined HashTable class
- Student should be able to define and compute the load factor of a hash table and implement a hash table that automatically resizes based on load factor

## [Technical Interview Tips I](../module/reczaVKTynSkqN8ZS)

#### Objectives:

- Student should be able to understand the typical interview process for a technical programming job
- Student should be able to recall best-practices and tips for technical interviews

## [Technical Interview Tips II](../module/rec6kEjLri9SXMYdE)

#### Objectives:

- Student should be able to recall strategies for getting "unstuck" during a technical interview
- Student should be able to recall strategies for overcoming imposter syndrome during a technical interview
